HEADWORD: Impark
<hw>Im*park"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Imparked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imparking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Empark</er>.]</ety> <def>To inclose for a park; to sever from a
common; hence, to inclose or shut up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They . . . <qex>impark</qex> them [the sheep] within hurdles.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

